C¶

1) In the first part, pca used by projecting to X2 axis, where the variance is bigger.

2) In both case we get similar graphs; however, I was expecting exactly the same graph for euclidian distance used MDS and PCA because in PCA algoritms tries to get biggest correlation, and in euclidian distance used MDS case algoritms tries to get the least distance.

3) It looks like MDS used cases give better result. However, It should be taken into account that if the dimension increases MDS might fail due to curse of dimensionality.
